## Lag Compensation

### Techniques

| Technique | Description | Use Case |
|-----------|-------------|----------|
| Client-side prediction | Predict local player | Local player movement |
| Server-side rewind | Server rewinds time for hit detection | Shooter hit registration |
| Interpolation | Smooth display of other entities | Other players, NPCs |
| Extrapolation | Guess movement until next update | High latency mitigation |

### Server-Side Rewind

For hit-scan or projectile hit detection: server stores past states. When processing shot, rewind to shooter's view at their latency, test against that historical state.

```
Player A shoots at tick 100 (client time)
Server receives at tick 105 (network delay)
Server rewinds to tick 100 state
Server tests hit against tick 100 positions
Server applies hit at tick 105
```

### Interpolation

Display other entities at time T - interpolation_delay. Smooth movement between received states. Delay adds latency to display but removes jitter.

- [ ] Interpolation delay: 100-200ms typical
- [ ] Extrapolate when no recent update (entity stopped?)
- [ ] Snap on teleport or large correction

