## Bandwidth Optimization

### Priorities

| Priority | Data | Rate | Compression |
|----------|------|------|-------------|
| Critical | Input, essential state | Every tick | Minimal |
| High | Position, rotation | 10-20 Hz | Quantize |
| Medium | Animation state, health | 5-10 Hz | Delta |
| Low | Cosmetic, effects | 1-5 Hz | Aggressive |

### Quantization

Reduce bits per value. Trade precision for bandwidth.

```cpp
// Position: 3 floats (12 bytes) -> 3 x 16-bit (6 bytes)
// Quantize to 0.01 unit precision over 655.35 unit range
uint16_t quantize(float v) {
    return (uint16_t)(v * 100.0f);
}
float dequantize(uint16_t v) {
    return (float)v / 100.0f;
}
```

### Bandwidth Budget

| Platform | Target | Per-Player |
|----------|--------|------------|
| PC | 128-256 kbps | |
| Console | 64-128 kbps | |
| Mobile | 32-64 kbps | |

### Checklist

- [ ] Delta compression for state updates
- [ ] Quantization for positions, rotations
- [ ] Rate limiting per data type
- [ ] Keyframes for full state recovery
- [ ] Bandwidth budget per platform

---

## Checklist

- [ ] Server is authoritative for game state
- [ ] Client prediction for local player
- [ ] Input history stored for reconciliation
- [ ] Rollback logic handles server correction
- [ ] Determinism verified (client matches server for same input)
- [ ] Delta compression for state updates
- [ ] Lag compensation strategy defined (rewind, interpolation)
- [ ] Bandwidth budget and quantization applied
